            <h1 style="text-align:center;">Short History</h1>
            <br />
            <p>Josef Rodenstock's belief was that vision defects are not a disease but can be corrected by using the right glasses. He developed his first viewing glasses in 1880 and they immediately started selling very well. From then until today, Rodenstock stock glasses are not cheap and compared to the ready-made glasses, common at that time, they were tried and made separately for each user of glasses.</p>
            <br />
